---
import { getCollection } from 'astro:content';
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import OptimizedImage from '../components/OptimizedImage.astro';
import FounderAvatar from '../components/FounderAvatar.astro';

// Single source of truth for founder profiles (shared with the homepage hero).
const founders = (await getCollection('team')).sort(
  (a, b) => a.data.order - b.data.order
);
---

<Layout title="About" description="Two operators, one studio. Here's how we work and why.">
  <section class="pt-28 md:pt-36 pb-16 px-4">
    <div class="container-custom max-w-desktop">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-[1fr_auto] gap-12 md:gap-16 items-start">
        <div>
          <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-subtle font-medium mb-3">
            Where the name comes from
          </p>
          <h1 class="font-tight text-4xl md:text-5xl font-semibold text-ink max-w-3xl leading-[1.1]">
            Inspired by a 17th-century metaphor. Driven by 21st-century
            intelligence.
          </h1>
          <div class="mt-8 max-w-2xl space-y-6 text-lg md:text-xl text-body leading-relaxed">
            <p>
              nuefunnel was born in Nuremberg, Germany &mdash; inspired by the
              <strong class="text-ink font-semibold">Nuremberg Funnel
              (Nürnberger Trichter)</strong>, a centuries-old metaphor for
              pouring knowledge directly into the mind. We loved that idea
              because it captures what we're trying to do with AI:
              <strong class="text-ink font-semibold">make complex things feel
              simple</strong>.
            </p>
            <p>
              One might call it context engineering or prompting skills,
              but ensuring that an AI solution has relevant knowledge about
              your business, processes and tools is the key to success. 
              We build
              <strong class="text-ink font-semibold">AI-native products and
              solutions</strong> that help businesses streamline processes,
              boost productivity, and unlock the full potential of modern AI.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <figure class="w-full max-w-[260px]">
          <OptimizedImage
            src="/images/uploads/nue-trichter.png"
            alt="1910 Nuremberg poster stamp depicting the Nuremberg funnel"
            class="w-full h-auto rounded-md border border-border shadow-sm"
            loading="eager"
          />
          <figcaption class="mt-3 text-xs text-subtle leading-relaxed">
            A 1910 Nuremberg poster stamp depicting the Nuremberg funnel, with
            the slogan:
            <span class="block mt-1 italic">
              &ldquo;If you lack wisdom in some matters, let them bring you the
              Funnel from Nuremberg.&rdquo;
            </span>
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="who-we-are" class="py-20 md:py-24 px-4 border-t border-border">
    <div class="container-custom max-w-desktop">
      <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-subtle font-medium mb-3">
        Who we are
      </p>
      <h2 class="font-tight text-3xl md:text-5xl font-semibold text-ink max-w-3xl leading-[1.1]">
        The two of us.
      </h2>

      <div class="mt-14 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 md:gap-16">
        {founders.map((f) => (
          <div>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-6">
              <FounderAvatar
                photo={f.data.photo}
                initials={f.data.initials}
                name={f.data.name}
                size="md"
              />
              <div>
                <p class="font-tight text-xl font-semibold text-ink leading-tight">
                  {f.data.name}
                </p>
                <p class="text-subtle text-sm mt-1">{f.data.role}</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="text-body leading-relaxed">
              {f.data.bio}
            </p>
            <div class="mt-5 flex flex-wrap gap-x-5 gap-y-2">
              {f.data.links.map((l) => (
                <a
                  href={l.href}
                  target="_blank"
                  rel="noopener noreferrer"
                  class="text-sm text-accent hover:text-accent-hover underline underline-offset-4 decoration-1"
                >
                  {l.label}
                </a>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-20 md:py-24 px-4 border-t border-border">
    <div class="container-custom max-w-desktop">
      <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-subtle font-medium mb-3">
        How we work
      </p>
      <h2 class="font-tight text-3xl md:text-5xl font-semibold text-ink max-w-3xl leading-[1.1]">
        Small scope, two people, coding-agent-assisted.
      </h2>

      <div class="mt-10 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 max-w-4xl">
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-tight text-xl font-semibold text-ink leading-snug mb-3">
            We engage in short cycles.
          </h3>
          <p class="text-body leading-relaxed">
            Four to eight weeks per project. We don't do indefinite staff
            augmentation. The end of an engagement is a real end - you
            get a running system, the infrastructure-as-code, and the context
            to run it.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-tight text-xl font-semibold text-ink leading-snug mb-3">
            We write code with coding agents.
          </h3>
          <p class="text-body leading-relaxed">
            Both of us use coding agents heavily. It's what makes a two-person
            team viable at this scope. We're opinionated about which parts of
            the work agents help with and which parts they don't.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-tight text-xl font-semibold text-ink leading-snug mb-3">
            We don't introduce new platforms.
          </h3>
          <p class="text-body leading-relaxed">
            Almost every engagement runs on top of the customer's existing
            warehouse, CRM, or doc system. New systems-of-record are a
            ten-person-team kind of project - not something we take on.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-tight text-xl font-semibold text-ink leading-snug mb-3">
            We turn down work that isn't a fit.
          </h3>
          <p class="text-body leading-relaxed">
            Enterprise compliance work, ML-platform builds, and projects that
            need a project manager between us and the decision-makers
            aren't a good fit for the studio. We say so up front.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-20 md:py-24 px-4 border-t border-border">
    <div class="container-custom max-w-desktop">
      <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-subtle font-medium mb-3">
        Get in touch
      </p>
      <h2 class="font-tight text-3xl md:text-5xl font-semibold text-ink max-w-3xl leading-[1.1]">
        Send a short note.
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-6 text-lg text-body max-w-2xl leading-relaxed">
        We’re proudly bootstrapped, deeply curious, and aim to deliver value. 
        Tell us what you have in mind and we'll reply within a couple of working days.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-8">
        <a
          href="mailto:contact@nuefunnel.com?subject=Project%20inquiry"
          class="btn-primary"
        >
          contact@nuefunnel.com
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
